{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/how-to-fix-python-ssl-certificate-verify-failed/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"itsopensource"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"1ea5dba8-0798-5f43-93e8-86f12cee41f4","excerpt":"Recently after upgrading the python version to , I started getting this error everytime I am running any python script. The reason behind this is Python 3.6 onâ€¦","html":"<p>Recently after upgrading the python version to <code class=\"language-text\">3.6</code>, I started getting this error everytime I am running any python script.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">[SSL: CERTIFICATE_VERIFY_FAILED] certificate verify failed (_ssl.c:726)&gt;</code></pre></div>\n<p>The reason behind this is Python 3.6 on MacOS uses an embedded version of OpenSSL, which does not use the system certificate store. More information <a href=\"https://bugs.python.org/issue28150\">here</a>.</p>\n<p>Quick fix for this problem on MacOS is to open Finder and double clicking <code class=\"language-text\">Install Certificates.command</code></p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;  max-width: 311px;\"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/21603b710f58cb7b25a20e0b38499ee5/184f6/1.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 61.09324758842444%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"1\"\n        title=\"1\"\n        src=\"/static/21603b710f58cb7b25a20e0b38499ee5/184f6/1.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/21603b710f58cb7b25a20e0b38499ee5/00d96/1.png 148w,\n/static/21603b710f58cb7b25a20e0b38499ee5/0b23c/1.png 295w,\n/static/21603b710f58cb7b25a20e0b38499ee5/184f6/1.png 311w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 311px) 100vw, 311px\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Or you can do this via terminal by:</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"text\"><pre class=\"language-text\"><code class=\"language-text\">open /Applications/Python\\ 3.6/Install\\ Certificates.command</code></pre></div>\n<p>Enjoy!</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"How to fix Python SSL CERTIFICATE_VERIFY_FAILED","tags":["python","ssl"],"date":"December 12, 2019","description":null,"author":"shivam"}}},"pageContext":{"isCreatedByStatefulCreatePages":false,"slug":"/how-to-fix-python-ssl-certificate-verify-failed/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/how-to-setup-irc-and-irc-bouncer/"},"frontmatter":{"author":"shivam","tags":["irc","bouncer"],"title":"How to setup IRC and IRC bouncer"}},"next":null}}}